FBIS4-14332 "drnes083_l_94011" FBIS-NES-94-083 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 ISRAEL Poll Conducted on Uprooting Settlements for Peace Poll Conducted on Uprooting Settlements for Peace TA2904105794 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 29 Apr 94 p 1 TA2904105794 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT Hebrew BFN [Poll by the Dafah Institute headed by Dr. Mina Zemah] [Text] The prime minister said: "Peace is more important for Israel's future and security than this or that group of settlements." Do you agree or disagree with that statement? Agree: 51 percent; Disagree: 45 percent; No comment: 4 percent. The prime minister continued: "I supported and will continue to support the removal of Golan settlements for the sake of peace." Do you agree or disagree with that position? Agree: 39 percent; Disagree: 58 percent; No comment: 3 percent. In your opinion, should the prime minister have made those remarks in public? Should have: 50 percent; Should not have: 47 percent; No comment: 3 percent. The poll was conducted on Tuesday and Wednesday among 547 interviewees, which make up a representative example of the adult population. Maximum margin of error is 4 percent.
